<em>=CE=BB=E1=B5=A2</em> =3D _=CF=83=E1=B5=A2_=C2=B2. In other words, the c=
olumns of <em>U</em> are eigenvectors of <em>AA=E1=B5=97.</em> Because the =
columns of <em>U</em> are orthonormal, the left-singular vectors of <em>A</=
