<li>Construct the matrix <em>A=E1=B5=97A</em>.</li>
<li>Compute the eigenvalues and eigenvectors of <em>A=E1=B5=97A</em>. The e=
igenvalues will be the squares of the singular values of <em>A</em>, and th=
e eigenvectors will form the columns of the matrix <em>V</em> in the SVD.</=
li>
<li>Arrange the singular values of <em>A</em> in descending order. Create a=
n <em>m</em> =C3=97 <em>n</em> diagonal matrix =CE=A3 with the singular val=
ues on the diagonal, padding with zeros if necessary so that the matrix has=
 the same dimensions as <em>A</em>.</li>
<li>Normalize the eigenvectors of <em>A=E1=B5=97A</em> to have unit length,=
 and place them as columns of matrix <em>V</em>.</li>
<li>For each singular value <em>=CF=83=E1=B5=A2</em>, calculate the corresp=
onding left-singular vector <strong>u</strong><em>=E1=B5=A2</em> as</li>
</ol>
