rresponding to eigenvalue 0 (sinc_e A_A</strong>=E1=B5=97<strong>x =3D </st=
rong>0=E2=8B=85<strong>x). To find an orthonormal basis fo<em>r</em> _N(_A=
=E1=B5=97), we first solve the homogenous linear syste<em>m</em> A</strong>=
=E1=B5=97<strong>x </strong>=3D** 0 to find a basis fo<em>r</em> _N(_A=E1=
=B5=97), then use the <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Gram%E2%80%9=
3Schmidt_process">Gram-Schmidt process</a> on this set of basis vectors to =
make them orthogonal, and finally we normalize them into unit vectors.</p>
<p class=3D"wp-block-paragraph">Another way to find the left-singular vecto=
rs of <em>A</em> (the columns of <em>U</em>) is to compute the eigenvectors=
